sentences: Malik Hall (born in 1996), better known by his stage name Haleek Maul, is an American rapper and record producer.
In 2012, Haleek Maul released his debut EP, Oxyconteen.
Spin named it the "Rap Release of the Week", while Fact placed it at number 48 on the "50 Best Albums of 2012" list.

In that year, he also released a collaborative mixtape with Chicago production duo Supreme Cuts, titled Chrome Lips.
Clash included it on the "Top 10 Mixtapes of the Year" list.
He released a mixtape, Prince Midas, in 2015, an EP, In Permanence, in 2018, and his debut solo studio album, Errol, in 2020.
